We have,<br><br>$${E_1} = \left\{ {x \in R:x \ne 1\,and\,{x \over {x - 1}} &gt; 0} \right\}$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ $${E_1} = {x \over {x - 1}} &gt; 0$$<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kx13g6z5/53a65f35-0d64-4508-a121-2823b8ac232b/3e317c10-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13g6z6.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kx13g6z5/53a65f35-0d64-4508-a121-2823b8ac232b/3e317c10-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13g6z6.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Mathematics - Functions Question 28 English Explanation 1"><br><br>$${E_1} = x \in ( - \infty ,0) \cup (1,\infty )$$<br><br>and $${E_2} = \left\{ \matrix{
  x \in {E_1}:{\sin ^{ - 1}}\left( {{{\log }_e}\left( {{x \over {x - 1}}} \right)} \right) \hfill \cr 
  is\,a\,real\,number \hfill \cr}  \right\}$$<br><br>$${E_2} =  - 1 \le {\log _e}{x \over {x - 1}} \le 1$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {e^{ - 1}} \le {x \over {x - 1}} \le e$$<br><br>Now, $${x \over {x - 1}} \ge {e^{ - 1}} \Rightarrow {x \over {x - 1}} - {1 \over e} \ge 0$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {{ex - x + 1} \over {e(x - 1)}} \ge 0 \Rightarrow {{x(e - 1) + 1} \over {(x - 1)e}} \ge 0$$<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kx13h996/f0f207a7-81ec-4124-8a83-1f50a710db54/5bc337a0-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13h997.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kx13h996/f0f207a7-81ec-4124-8a83-1f50a710db54/5bc337a0-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13h997.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Mathematics - Functions Question 28 English Explanation 2"><br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x \in \left( { - \infty ,\,{1 \over {1 - e}}} \right) \cup (1,\infty )$$<br><br>Also, $${x \over {x - 1}} \le e$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow {{(e - 1)x - e} \over {x - 1}} \ge 0$$<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kx13iisa/63110af1-7566-42aa-b0fc-b795326bccb6/7eef1fa0-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13iisb.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kx13iisa/63110af1-7566-42aa-b0fc-b795326bccb6/7eef1fa0-5a1b-11ec-9197-413c7acc42fc/file-1kx13iisb.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Mathematics - Functions Question 28 English Explanation 3"><br><br>$$ \Rightarrow x \in ( - \infty ,\,1) \cup \left[ {{e \over {e - 1}},\infty } \right)$$<br><br>So, $${E_2} = \left( { - \infty ,\,{1 \over {1 - e}}} \right] \cup \left[ {{e \over {e - 1}},\,\infty } \right)$$<br><br>$$ \therefore $$ The domain of f and g are<br><br>$$\left( { - \infty ,\,{1 \over {1 - e}}} \right] \cup \left[ {{e \over {e - 1}},\,\infty } \right)$$<br><br>and Range of $${x \over {x - 1}}$$ is R<sup>+</sup> $$-$$ {1}<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow $$ Range of f is R $$-$$ {0} or ($$-$$$$\infty $$, 0) $$ \cup $$ (0, $$\infty $$)<br><br>Range of g is $$\left[ { - {\pi  \over 2},{\pi  \over 2}} \right] - \{ 0\} $$ or $$\left[ { - {\pi  \over 2},0} \right) \cup \left( {0,{\pi  \over 2}} \right]$$<br><br>Now, P $$ \to $$ 4, Q $$ \to $$ 2, R $$ \to $$ 1, S $$ \to $$ 1<br><br>Hence, option (a) is correct answer.

